    "summary_one_sentence": "As a new school year begins at Truham-Higgs, Nick and Charlie's relationship grows deeper while they contemplate their lives beyond graduation.",
    "summary_short": "Heartstopper Forever follows the Truham-Higgs friend group as they return for a new school year. Nick and Charlie's romantic relationship continues to deepen amid the everyday highs and lows of sixth form life. The couple begins to think seriously about what comes after school ends and how their future might look together. Their friends also navigate their own personal growth, relationships, and uncertainties about the road ahead.",
    "summary_long": "Heartstopper Forever opens with the Truham-Higgs gang reuniting for the start of a new school year, bringing fresh energy and familiar comfort to their friendships. Nick and Charlie, now more secure in their relationship, find their bond deepening as they face new academic and social challenges together. As the months pass, the couple begins to seriously consider life after the final school bell, weighing dreams of university, living arrangements, and staying close despite impending change. Charlie continues to manage his mental health with Nick's steady support, showing the quiet strength of their partnership. Meanwhile, Tara and Darcy navigate the complexities of their own relationship, learning to communicate through misunderstandings and growth. Elle adjusts to life at Lambert and her evolving artistic ambitions, while Tao and Isaac explore their identities and friendships in new ways. The group leans on one another through exam stress, family expectations, and the bittersweet awareness that childhood is ending. Small moments—study sessions, walks, celebrations—highlight how far they have all come. By the close of the year, Nick and Charlie feel more certain about facing the future together, even with unknowns ahead. The story affirms that love and friendship can anchor young people as they step into adulthood.",
